ZH: 我的嗅觉很敏锐，能够闻到最微弱的气味。
EN: My sense of smell is very acute, I can detect the faintest odors.

ZH: 这个花园里的花香让我非常享受我的嗅觉。
EN: The scent of the flowers in this garden is a great pleasure for my sense of smell.

ZH: 狗的嗅觉比人类敏锐得多，可以嗅到许多我们闻不到的气味。
EN: Dogs have a much more keen sense of smell than humans and can detect many odors that we cannot.

ZH: 被咖啡店的香气包围着，我立刻感到我的嗅觉变得更加敏感了。
EN: Surrounded by the aroma of the coffee shop, I immediately felt my sense of smell becoming more sensitive.

ZH: 这种花的香味非常特别，让人立刻爱上它的嗅觉。
EN: The scent of this flower is very unique, it captivates one's sense of smell instantly.

ZH: 这个餐馆的菜肴散发出美味的香气，让人嗅觉大开。
EN: The dishes in this restaurant emit a delicious aroma that stimulates one's sense of smell.

ZH: 足球场上草坪的气味让我回忆起了美好的童年，是我最喜欢的嗅觉之一。
EN: The smell of the grass on the soccer field brings back fond memories of my childhood, it is one of my favorite smells.

ZH: 新鲜出炉的面包散发出的香气能够勾起人们的嗅觉和食欲。
EN: The aroma of freshly baked bread can awaken people's sense of smell and appetite.

ZH: 没有味道的食物对于味觉来说没有吸引力，但对嗅觉也是一种挑战。
EN: Tasteless food lacks appeal to the sense of taste, but it also presents a challenge to the sense of smell.

ZH: 嗅觉是我们五感之一，它能使我们感受到周围世界的气味。
EN: Smell is one of our five senses, it allows us to perceive the odors of the surrounding world.

ZH: 嗅觉能够在记忆中唤起某种味道，一闻到那个味道，瞬间回想起那段时光。
EN: Smell can evoke a certain taste in memory, just a whiff of that scent and it instantly brings back that period of time.

ZH: 在春天的花园散步，能够聆听到不同花朵的芳香，同时启发嗅觉。
EN: Taking a walk in the spring garden, one can listen to the fragrances of different flowers and at the same time awaken the sense of smell.

ZH: 嗅觉对于动物来说尤为重要，它帮助它们识别食物、追踪猎物以及辨别潜在危险。
EN: The sense of smell is particularly important for animals, as it helps them identify food, track prey, and discern potential danger.

ZH: 露营的时候，空气中散发出野外的味道，唤起我的嗅觉和冒险精神。
EN: When camping, the air emits the wild scent, awakening my sense of smell and spirit of adventure.

ZH: 物质刺激能够引起我们的嗅觉，并激发我们对环境变化的注意力。
EN: Sensory stimulation can trigger our sense of smell and arouse our attention to changes in the environment.

ZH: 嗅觉在感知食物和饮品的口味方面扮演着重要的角色。
EN: The sense of smell plays a crucial role in perceiving the taste of food and beverages.

ZH: 我的嗅觉变得敏感的时候，我闻到了一股烟味。
EN: When my sense of smell became sensitive, I caught a whiff of smoke.

ZH: 新鲜的水果给人们的嗅觉带来清新的味道。
EN: Fresh fruits bring a refreshing aroma to people's sense of smell.

ZH: 烹饪的美食散发出的香气使人垂涎欲滴，引起了我的嗅觉。
EN: The aroma emanating from the cooking delicacies is mouthwatering, it stimulates my sense of smell.

ZH: 潮湿的土壤散发出独特的气息，我通过嗅觉可以感受到大地的气息。
EN: The damp soil emits a unique scent, through my sense of smell I can sense the breath of the earth.
